 Duke University Logo
Duke University is a private research university in Durham, North Carolina. Founded by Methodists and Quakers in the present-day town of Trinity in 1838, the school moved to Durham in 1892. In 1924, tobacco and electric power industrialist James Buchanan Duke established The Duke Endowment and the institution changed its name to honor his deceased father, Washington Duke. Duke’s campus spans over 8,600 acres on three contiguous sub-campuses in Durham as well as a marine lab in Beaufort.

item.title: Duke
item.description: Duke University is a private research university in Durham, North Carolina. Founded by Methodists and Quakers in the present-day town of Trinity in 1838, the school moved to Durham in 1892. In 1924, tobacco and electric power industrialist James Buchanan Duke established The Duke Endowment and the institution changed its name to honor his deceased father, Washington Duke. Duke’s campus spans over 8,600 acres on three contiguous sub-campuses in Durham as well as a marine lab in Beaufort.
